<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Risk_mim  Entity: risk_attitude  
   <express_ref linkend="risk:mim:Risk_mim.risk_attitude"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Risk_mim.risk_attitude">
A <b>risk_attitude</b> is a factor that helps weigh the criticality of the 
<express_ref linkend="risk:mim:Risk_mim.risk_level"/>.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Risk_mim  Entity: risk_attitude  Attribute: name 
   <express_ref linkend="risk:mim:Risk_mim.risk_attitude.name"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Risk_mim.risk_attitude.criticality_factor">
numerical value representing the criticallity of the <express_ref linkend="risk:mim:Risk_mim.risk_attitude"/>. 
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Risk_mim  Entity: risk_attitude  Attribute: description 
   <express_ref linkend="risk:mim:Risk_mim.risk_attitude.description"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Risk_mim.risk_attitude.description">
the text that provides further information about the <express_ref linkend="risk:mim:Risk_mim.risk_attitude"/>. 
The value of the attribute need not be specified.

</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Risk_mim  Entity: risk_characterized_object  
   <express_ref linkend="risk:mim:Risk_mim.risk_characterized_object"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Risk_mim.risk_characterized_object">
A <b>risk_characterized_object</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="risk_schema:ir_express:risk_schema.risk"/>. 
A <b>risk_characterized_object</b> assigns property to <express_ref linkend="risk_schema:ir_express:risk_schema.risk"/>. 
This assignment allows properties unique to when a <express_ref linkend="risk_schema:ir_express:risk_schema.risk"/> 
is assigned to product or activity data to define its <express_ref linkend="risk_schema:ir_express:risk_schema.risk"/>. 

</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Risk_mim  Entity: risk_level  
   <express_ref linkend="risk:mim:Risk_mim.risk_level"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Risk_mim.risk_level">
A <b>risk_level</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="risk_schema:ir_express:risk_schema.risk_perception"/> that has an identifiable goal or objective.  
<note>
A <express_ref linkend="risk:mim:Risk_mim.risk_level"/> is described by its
<express_ref linkend="risk:mim:Risk_mim.risk_attitude"/> and <express_ref linkend="risk:mim:Risk_mim.risk_objective"/>.
</note>
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Risk_mim  Entity: risk_level  Attribute: risk_attitude 
   <express_ref linkend="risk:mim:Risk_mim.risk_level.criticality_factor"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Risk_mim.risk_level.risk_attitude">

the identifiable <express_ref linkend="risk:mim:Risk_mim.risk_attitude"/> by which a 
<express_ref linkend="risk:mim:Risk_mim.risk_level"/> is assessed.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Risk_mim  Entity: risk_level  Attribute: risk_objective 
   <express_ref linkend="risk:mim:Risk_mim.risk_level.risk_objective"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Risk_mim.risk_level.risk_objective">

the identifiable goal of a <express_ref linkend="risk:mim:Risk_mim.risk_level"/>.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Risk_mim  Entity: risk_level_relationship  
   <express_ref linkend="risk:mim:Risk_mim.risk_level_relationship"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Risk_mim.risk_level_relationship">
A <b>risk_level_relationship</b> is a type of 
<express_ref linkend="risk_schema:ir_express:risk_schema.risk_perception_relationship"/> that associates two instances of
<express_ref linkend="risk:mim:Risk_mim.risk_level"/>.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Risk_mim  Entity: risk_level_relationship  Attribute: relating_risk_level 
   <express_ref linkend="risk:mim:Risk_mim.risk_level_relationship.relating_risk_level"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Risk_mim.risk_level_relationship.relating_risk_level">
one of the instances of 
<express_ref linkend="risk:mim:Risk_mim.risk_level_relationship"/> 
that is a part of the relationship. 
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Risk_mim  Entity: risk_level_relationship  Attribute: related_risk_level 
   <express_ref linkend="risk:mim:Risk_mim.risk_level_relationship.related_risk_level"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Risk_mim.risk_level_relationship.related_risk_level">

the other of the instances of 
<express_ref linkend="risk:mim:Risk_mim.risk_level_relationship"/> 
that is a part of the relationship. 
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Risk_mim  Entity: risk_objective  
   <express_ref linkend="risk:mim:Risk_mim.risk_objective"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Risk_mim.risk_objective">
A <b>risk_objective</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="risk_schema:ir_express:risk_schema.risk_context"/>
that places a context for <express_ref linkend="risk:mim:Risk_mim.risk_level"/> assessments.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Risk_mim  Entity: risk_profile  
   <express_ref linkend="risk:mim:Risk_mim.risk_profile"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Risk_mim.risk_profile">
A <b>risk_profile</b> is an identifiable set or <express_ref linkend="risk:mim:Risk_mim.risk_profile.history"/> of two or more instances of 
<express_ref linkend="risk_schema:ir_express:risk_schema.risk_status"/>.

</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Risk_mim  Entity: risk_profile  Attribute: name 
   <express_ref linkend="risk:mim:Risk_mim.risk_profile.name"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Risk_mim.risk_profile.name">

the label by which the <express_ref linkend="risk:mim:Risk_mim.risk_profile"/> is known. 
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Risk_mim  Entity: risk_profile  Attribute: description 
   <express_ref linkend="risk:mim:Risk_mim.risk_profile.description"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Risk_mim.risk_profile.description">

the text that provides further information about the <express_ref linkend="risk:mim:Risk_mim.risk_profile"/>. 
The value of the attribute need not be specified. 
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Risk_mim  Entity: risk_profile  Attribute: history 
   <express_ref linkend="risk:mim:Risk_mim.risk_profile.history"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Risk_mim.risk_profile.history">

the identifiable set of two or more instances of <express_ref linkend="risk_schema:ir_express:risk_schema.risk_status"/>.
</ext_description>
